#: ../../source/manual/backups.rst:9
msgid "Backup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/backups.rst:11
msgid ""
"You can backup and restore your machines configuration using the "
":menuselection:`System --> Configuration --> Backups` section. When "
"performing a local backup, you can choose to protect it with a password "
"and decide whether or not you would like to store rrd statistics as well "
"(in which case they will be stored in the same export xml file)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/backups.rst:17
msgid ""
"Due to the sensitive nature of your configuration data, its advisable to "
"protect backups with a strong password when storing them or distributing "
"them to others."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/backups.rst:22
msgid "RRD statistics are used in System Health"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/backups.rst:25
msgid ""
"Restoring backups can either be performed partially or for the complete "
"configuration. Since configurations usually have various components that "
"depend on each other, it's most safe to restore a complete configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/backups.rst:30
msgid ""
"Partial restores can lead to unexpected behavior, use with care. Future "
"versions might not support this feature due to consistency reasons. (not "
"all components can be partially exported)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/backups.rst:44
msgid "Defaults"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/backups.rst:46
msgid ""
"With the defaults tool you can reset your firewall back to firmware "
"defaults and shutdown when done."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/backups.rst:51
msgid "History"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/backups.rst:53
msgid ""
"The history menu helps you track changes between modifications and offer "
"the opportunity to download older versions of your settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/backups.rst:58
msgid ""
"You can specify the number of backups to keep in this menu, which can be "
"quite practical when a higher level of auditability is required."
msgstr ""

